    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a benchmark-tier 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S, maintaining full mechanical integrity and aesthetic excellence. This 996.2 iteration features the M96/03 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six with VarioCam Plus, delivering a linear power band and crisp throttle response. The G96/31 6-speed manual transaxle offers precise gate engagement, paired with the factory viscous-coupling AWD system for superior lateral grip. This example has been meticulously preserved; the IMS bearing has been upgraded with an LN Engineering dual-row ceramic solution, and the rear main seal (RMS) remains bone dry. The wide-body chassis retains its original rigidity, riding on a refreshed suspension with zero bushing deflection. Braking is handled by Turbo-spec four-piston monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing no signs of thermal stress. A truly turn-key, concours-standard specimen for the discerning collector.",
      "price": 48500.0,
